Louis Jordan, 37, was picked up by a German ship off the North Carolina coast on Thursday after he took off to do some fishing on January 23 . 
  He was found sitting on the capsized hull of his sailboat that had lost its mast and was 200 miles east of Cape Hatteras . 
  He suffered a broken collarbone and dehydration but survived by drinking rain water and eating raw fish . 
  His mother Norma said she had given up hope 'many times' He was released from hospital in Norfolk on Friday . 
 